158H</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/Digital_object_identifier\" title=\"Digital object identifier\">doi</a>:<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//doi.org/10.1038/304158a0\">10.1038/304158a0</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Nature&amp;rft.atitle=%3Cspan+class%3D%22nowrap%22%3E+%3C%2Fspan%3E%E2%80%98Unlearning%E2%80%99+has+a+stabilizing+effect+in+collective+memories&amp;rft.volume=304&amp;rft.pages=158-159&amp;rft.date=1983-07-14&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1038%2F304158a0&amp;rft_id=info%3Abibcode%2F1983Natur.304..158H&amp;rft.au=Hopfield%2C+John++J.&amp;rft.au=Feinstein%2C+David+I.&amp;rft.au=Palmer%2C+Richard+G.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AReverse+learning\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation journal\">Brown (1996). \"Autism, Asperger's syndrome and the Crick-Mitchison theory of the biological function of REM sleep\". <i><a href=\"/wiki/Medical_Hypotheses\" title=\"Medical Hypotheses\">Medical Hypotheses</a></i>. <b>47</b> (5): 399\u2013403. <a href=\"/wiki/Digital_object_identifier\" title=\"Digital object identifier\">doi</a>:<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//doi.org/10.1016/S0306-9877%2896%2990220-0\">10.1016/S0306-9877(96)90220-0</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/PubMed_Identifier\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"PubMed Identifier\">PMID</a>&#160;<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/8951804\">8951804</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Medical+Hypotheses&amp;rft.atitle=Autism%2C+Asperger%27s+syndrome+and+the+Crick-Mitchison+theory+of+the+biological+function+of+REM+sleep&amp;rft.volume=47&amp;rft.